<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="222" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,926,1995]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1034,1059]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Description.</emphasis>
<typeStatus box="[351,455,1034,1059]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Holotype</typeStatus>
complete specimen, 
<quantity box="[692,771,1034,1058]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8" pageId="21" pageNumber="222" unit="mm" value="28.0">28 mm</quantity>
long, 0.52 mm wide, with 177 chaetigers; 
<typeStatus box="[1250,1347,1035,1059]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">paratype</typeStatus>
smaller and incomplete. Body extremely long and slender, markedly cylindrical, without any colour pattern. Prostomium pentagonal; 4 small eyes in open trapezoidal arrangement and 2 minute anterior eyespots. Palps triangular, similar in length to prostomium (
<figureCitation box="[434,515,1142,1167]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1945,1967]" captionTargetBox="[205,1344,196,1899]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[205,1364,193,1926]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 12. Syllis marceloi, n. sp. (AM W. 48547 Holotype). A, anterior end, dorsal view. B, mid-posterior parapodium, lateral view. C, detail of distal part of parapodial lobe, dorsal view. D, dorsal simple chaeta. E, ventral simple chaeta. Scale bars: A: 0.4 mm. B, C: 0.1 mm. D, E: 20 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/343768/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
A). Median antenna arising between posterior eyes, short, slender, with 15 articles; lateral antennae similar to median one, but shorter, with 12–13 articles. Peristomium shorter than subsequent segments, dorsally covering posterior part of prostomium (
<figureCitation box="[826,910,1214,1239]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1945,1967]" captionTargetBox="[205,1344,196,1899]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[205,1364,193,1926]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 12. Syllis marceloi, n. sp. (AM W. 48547 Holotype). A, anterior end, dorsal view. B, mid-posterior parapodium, lateral view. C, detail of distal part of parapodial lobe, dorsal view. D, dorsal simple chaeta. E, ventral simple chaeta. Scale bars: A: 0.4 mm. B, C: 0.1 mm. D, E: 20 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/343768/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
A). Dorsal tentacular cirri longer than median antenna, with about 17 articles; ventral tentacular cirri with 12 articles. Dorsal parapodial cirri slender, short, with few articles (
<figureCitation box="[303,389,1286,1311]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1945,1967]" captionTargetBox="[205,1344,196,1899]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[205,1364,193,1926]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 12. Syllis marceloi, n. sp. (AM W. 48547 Holotype). A, anterior end, dorsal view. B, mid-posterior parapodium, lateral view. C, detail of distal part of parapodial lobe, dorsal view. D, dorsal simple chaeta. E, ventral simple chaeta. Scale bars: A: 0.4 mm. B, C: 0.1 mm. D, E: 20 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/343768/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
B), shorter than body width, with some internal inclusions (
<figureCitation box="[1086,1171,1286,1311]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1945,1967]" captionTargetBox="[205,1344,196,1899]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[205,1364,193,1926]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 12. Syllis marceloi, n. sp. (AM W. 48547 Holotype). A, anterior end, dorsal view. B, mid-posterior parapodium, lateral view. C, detail of distal part of parapodial lobe, dorsal view. D, dorsal simple chaeta. E, ventral simple chaeta. Scale bars: A: 0.4 mm. B, C: 0.1 mm. D, E: 20 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/343768/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
B); anteriormost dorsal parapodial cirri slightly shorter than dorsal tentacular cirri, with about 19–20 articles alternating with shorter ones, with about 12 articles; from midbody backwards, alternating long (about 15 articles) and short (about 10 articles) dorsal parapodial cirri. Parapodia conical, distally bilobed (
<figureCitation box="[812,893,1394,1419]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1945,1967]" captionTargetBox="[205,1344,196,1899]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[205,1364,193,1926]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 12. Syllis marceloi, n. sp. (AM W. 48547 Holotype). A, anterior end, dorsal view. B, mid-posterior parapodium, lateral view. C, detail of distal part of parapodial lobe, dorsal view. D, dorsal simple chaeta. E, ventral simple chaeta. Scale bars: A: 0.4 mm. B, C: 0.1 mm. D, E: 20 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/343768/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
B, C). Ventral parapodial cirri digitiform, shorter than parapodial lobes (
<figureCitation box="[406,489,1430,1455]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1945,1967]" captionTargetBox="[205,1344,196,1899]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[205,1364,193,1926]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 12. Syllis marceloi, n. sp. (AM W. 48547 Holotype). A, anterior end, dorsal view. B, mid-posterior parapodium, lateral view. C, detail of distal part of parapodial lobe, dorsal view. D, dorsal simple chaeta. E, ventral simple chaeta. Scale bars: A: 0.4 mm. B, C: 0.1 mm. D, E: 20 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/343768/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
B). Compound chaetae with short blades, bidentate with proximal tooth smaller than distal one (
<figureCitation box="[277,359,1466,1491]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="23.[151,250,1881,1903]" captionTargetBox="[155,1418,211,1846]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[151,1436,193,1859]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 13. Syllis marceloi, n. sp. (AM W. 48547 Holotype). A, compound chaetae, anterior parapodium. B, compound chaetae, midbody parapodium. C, compound chaetae, posterior parapodium. D, aciculae, anterior parapodium. E, aciculae, midbody parapodium. F, acicula, posterior parapodium. vScale bar: 20 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/343769/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
A, B), except on posterior parapodia, where the proximal tooth is slightly larger (
<figureCitation box="[1284,1365,1466,1491]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="23.[151,250,1881,1903]" captionTargetBox="[155,1418,211,1846]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[151,1436,193,1859]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 13. Syllis marceloi, n. sp. (AM W. 48547 Holotype). A, compound chaetae, anterior parapodium. B, compound chaetae, midbody parapodium. C, compound chaetae, posterior parapodium. D, aciculae, anterior parapodium. E, aciculae, midbody parapodium. F, acicula, posterior parapodium. vScale bar: 20 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/343769/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
A–C); spines on margin of blades short, except distal 1–3, which reach the level of proximal tooth (
<figureCitation box="[1185,1264,1502,1527]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="23.[151,250,1881,1903]" captionTargetBox="[155,1418,211,1846]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[151,1436,193,1859]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 13. Syllis marceloi, n. sp. (AM W. 48547 Holotype). A, compound chaetae, anterior parapodium. B, compound chaetae, midbody parapodium. C, compound chaetae, posterior parapodium. D, aciculae, anterior parapodium. E, aciculae, midbody parapodium. F, acicula, posterior parapodium. vScale bar: 20 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/343769/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
A–C). Anterior parapodia each with about 15 compound chaetae, blades 20 µm long above, 16 µm long below (
<figureCitation box="[1313,1399,1538,1563]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="23.[151,250,1881,1903]" captionTargetBox="[155,1418,211,1846]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[151,1436,193,1859]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 13. Syllis marceloi, n. sp. (AM W. 48547 Holotype). A, compound chaetae, anterior parapodium. B, compound chaetae, midbody parapodium. C, compound chaetae, posterior parapodium. D, aciculae, anterior parapodium. E, aciculae, midbody parapodium. F, acicula, posterior parapodium. vScale bar: 20 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/343769/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
A); midbody parapodia each with 6–7 compound chaetae, blades 26 µm long above, 16 µm long below (
<figureCitation box="[1318,1402,1574,1599]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="23.[151,250,1881,1903]" captionTargetBox="[155,1418,211,1846]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[151,1436,193,1859]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 13. Syllis marceloi, n. sp. (AM W. 48547 Holotype). A, compound chaetae, anterior parapodium. B, compound chaetae, midbody parapodium. C, compound chaetae, posterior parapodium. D, aciculae, anterior parapodium. E, aciculae, midbody parapodium. F, acicula, posterior parapodium. vScale bar: 20 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/343769/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
B); posterior parapodia each with 6 compound chaetae, blades 25 µm long above, 20 µm long below (
<figureCitation box="[1241,1321,1610,1635]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="23.[151,250,1881,1903]" captionTargetBox="[155,1418,211,1846]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[151,1436,193,1859]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 13. Syllis marceloi, n. sp. (AM W. 48547 Holotype). A, compound chaetae, anterior parapodium. B, compound chaetae, midbody parapodium. C, compound chaetae, posterior parapodium. D, aciculae, anterior parapodium. E, aciculae, midbody parapodium. F, acicula, posterior parapodium. vScale bar: 20 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/343769/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
C). Dorsal simple chaetae on posterior parapodia only, relatively thick, unidentate, smooth (
<figureCitation box="[1058,1139,1646,1671]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1945,1967]" captionTargetBox="[205,1344,196,1899]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[205,1364,193,1926]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 12. Syllis marceloi, n. sp. (AM W. 48547 Holotype). A, anterior end, dorsal view. B, mid-posterior parapodium, lateral view. C, detail of distal part of parapodial lobe, dorsal view. D, dorsal simple chaeta. E, ventral simple chaeta. Scale bars: A: 0.4 mm. B, C: 0.1 mm. D, E: 20 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/343768/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
D). Ventral simple chaetae on far posterior segments only, thick, bidentate, with proximal tooth larger than distal one, with smooth margin (
<figureCitation box="[159,241,1718,1743]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1945,1967]" captionTargetBox="[205,1344,196,1899]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[205,1364,193,1926]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 12. Syllis marceloi, n. sp. (AM W. 48547 Holotype). A, anterior end, dorsal view. B, mid-posterior parapodium, lateral view. C, detail of distal part of parapodial lobe, dorsal view. D, dorsal simple chaeta. E, ventral simple chaeta. Scale bars: A: 0.4 mm. B, C: 0.1 mm. D, E: 20 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/343768/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
E). Anterior aciculae very thick, distally rounded, emerging from parapodial lobes, numbering about 5 per parapodium (
<figureCitation box="[300,380,1754,1779]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="23.[151,250,1881,1903]" captionTargetBox="[155,1418,211,1846]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[151,1436,193,1859]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 13. Syllis marceloi, n. sp. (AM W. 48547 Holotype). A, compound chaetae, anterior parapodium. B, compound chaetae, midbody parapodium. C, compound chaetae, posterior parapodium. D, aciculae, anterior parapodium. E, aciculae, midbody parapodium. F, acicula, posterior parapodium. vScale bar: 20 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/343769/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
D); number and shape of aciculae progressively decreasing towards posterior end; in midbody parapodia, 2 straight pointed aciculae, one being slender, and the other distinctly large, protruding from parapodial lobes (
<figureCitation box="[235,325,1826,1851]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="23.[151,250,1881,1903]" captionTargetBox="[155,1418,211,1846]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[151,1436,193,1859]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 13. Syllis marceloi, n. sp. (AM W. 48547 Holotype). A, compound chaetae, anterior parapodium. B, compound chaetae, midbody parapodium. C, compound chaetae, posterior parapodium. D, aciculae, anterior parapodium. E, aciculae, midbody parapodium. F, acicula, posterior parapodium. vScale bar: 20 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/343769/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
E), becoming distally oblique in posterior parapodia (
<figureCitation box="[993,1084,1826,1851]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1945,1967]" captionTargetBox="[205,1344,196,1899]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[205,1364,193,1926]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 12. Syllis marceloi, n. sp. (AM W. 48547 Holotype). A, anterior end, dorsal view. B, mid-posterior parapodium, lateral view. C, detail of distal part of parapodial lobe, dorsal view. D, dorsal simple chaeta. E, ventral simple chaeta. Scale bars: A: 0.4 mm. B, C: 0.1 mm. D, E: 20 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/343768/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
B, C); one single acicula in posteriormost parapodia, being distinctly large, with oblique tip, and protruding from parapodial lobes (
<figureCitation box="[1323,1405,1862,1887]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="23.[151,250,1881,1903]" captionTargetBox="[155,1418,211,1846]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[151,1436,193,1859]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 13. Syllis marceloi, n. sp. (AM W. 48547 Holotype). A, compound chaetae, anterior parapodium. B, compound chaetae, midbody parapodium. C, compound chaetae, posterior parapodium. D, aciculae, anterior parapodium. E, aciculae, midbody parapodium. F, acicula, posterior parapodium. vScale bar: 20 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/343769/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
F). Pharynx distinctly long, slender, through more than 20 segments (
<quantity box="[896,955,1898,1923]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.318" pageId="21" pageNumber="222" unit="in" value="17.0">17 in</quantity>
<typeStatus box="[962,1062,1899,1923]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">paratype</typeStatus>
; everted in 
<typeStatus box="[1194,1294,1898,1923]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">holotype</typeStatus>
) (
<figureCitation box="[1318,1400,1898,1923]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="22.[151,250,1945,1967]" captionTargetBox="[205,1344,196,1899]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[205,1364,193,1926]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 12. Syllis marceloi, n. sp. (AM W. 48547 Holotype). A, anterior end, dorsal view. B, mid-posterior parapodium, lateral view. C, detail of distal part of parapodial lobe, dorsal view. D, dorsal simple chaeta. E, ventral simple chaeta. Scale bars: A: 0.4 mm. B, C: 0.1 mm. D, E: 20 µm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/343768/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
A); pharyngeal tooth on anterior margin of pharynx. Proventricle through 16 segments (
<quantity box="[1086,1143,1934,1959]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.302" pageId="21" pageNumber="222" unit="in" value="13.0">13 in</quantity>
<typeStatus box="[1150,1251,1935,1959]" pageId="21" pageNumber="222">paratype</typeStatus>
), with about 48– 50 muscle cell rows. Pygidium with 2 anal cirri, with 20 articles each, and a median stylus.
</paragraph>
